values:
Heh, I've been lazy about my posts because <lj user="quikchange"> has been posting for me.  Mwahahahahhaha!!  Well, anyways, I'm taking his position and making a post.  

I woke up high from anti-histamines... I'm not even sure they did anything.  But it was quite fun.  Especially when I made all the phones go off and I started throwing them at <lj user="quikchange">, screaming FIX IT FIX IT!

Later, we met up with <lj user="aciddawn"> in downtown Vancouver yesterday.  Shortly after, he got approached by a crack addicted at the Granville Burger King while <lj user="quikchange"> was on the hunt for a public washroom.
CA: Do you have $2?
AD: No.
CA: Do you have $5?
Ad: No. I need to go to an ATM for that.
CA: Do you want a blow job?

Then when we told the story to my dad:
Dad: She wanted to pay you 5 dollars to give a blowjob?
AD: No, she wanted $5 to give me a blowjob.
Dad: Did she have teeth?
Because obviously, you don't want a crack addict with teeth to give a blow job (ouchy)

We got lost in the rain in Vancouver yesterday as I had no idea how to take the bus home.  Ah ha.  Ha . ha . ha . (siiigh)

What else what else....  well, I met my pathological liar friend who's getting married this week.  She "forgot" my invitation "again" just like how she decided "not" to go on her honeymoon to Mexico that she "bought".  She is also the one who "quit" from the local grocery store because it was "not challenging enough" but actually got fired for stealing.  However, she has a fiancee that looks Ewan McGregor.  Frick.  I have no idea how she does it.  

We went to the Flying Beaver Airport Bar and Grill for lunch.  The waitress who served us had boobs that almost compared to Pamela Anderson's.

I almost got into a drinking related accident at 1 o'clock in the afternoon.  This is a contract that I will never EVER drive again under the influence any cocktail drink. Especially especially Coke and Rum.  Ughhhh.  Yes, if I ever drive under rum again you must never EVER be my friend again in the real or virtual worlds.

<lj user="quikchange"> wanted to see the seedy part of Vancouver so I brought him as far down Hastings Street as I dared.  Two blocks past Main St and then back through Chinatown.  <lj user="Aciddawn"> didn't want to come with us to the <del>Gastown</del> PickPocketing Capital of Canada so we left him at the SeaBus station.  He never returned my text so we assumed something crazy and zany occured.  Fortunately, we didn't get pickpocketed and <lj user="quikchange"> bought a dino for $4.  Unfortunately, we didn't get any blowjobs.  

After oogling the homeless, the drugged and the police watching them, we met <lj user="krabbit"> at the Vancouver Public Library.  <lj user="quikchange"> was in desperate need of Gatorade, which scared me because Gatorade scares me in general and the idea of <lj user="quikchange"> hyper scares me even more.  But luckily he bought the clear kind and the promptly fell asleep up in the Special Collections floor in VPL.  I don't understand why not more people visit the 6th floor of VPL because it's practically a free museum.  I saw the majority of the photos we paid $8.95 to see at Georgia Gulf Cannery in the photobooks there as well as the attempt to destroy Chinatown, the Japanese Holding Station in Hastings before they were shipped out the Interior, the old downtown where all the homeless people live now, old Hotel Vancouver, the incompleted freeway plan through Vancouver (wooo for civil uproar), and the planning of the Expo grounds.  The Special Collections also have ridiculously cheap photos for sale.  They aren't the coolest of pictures, but they're still cheaper and nicer than anything else you'll find in Gastown.

After that, I continued my search for calf-high boots and fuzzy accessories.
I failed.

However, we went down to where the old seedy part of Vancouver used to be located, where now the Faggiest Rainbow Street in Western Canada is.  <lj user="krabbit"> and I found the most awesome clothing store ever!!  And it is my little secret so you will just have to brave the fags and queers and find it.  I screeched at delight when I saw the clothes and I screeched even more when the prices were actually reasonable.  It was clothing heaven.

Then we went to Little Sisters Bookstore which has the most awesome assortment of books, dildos, butt plugs and rainbow bracelets.  (They mostly sell books.  I promise.  But the owner will give a full "evaluation" when you make a purchase)

Oh yes, <lj user="quikchange"> got checked out more times than he checked out white ipod headphones in downtown.  I won't give offical statistics because I don't have eyes on the back of my head, but the ipods lost ridiculously badly.

<lj user="quikchange"> just read my entry and now he wants me to do all of them.  But no no no. I just have humour right now, and it will be rotten and sour by tomorrow morning.

<lj-cut text="Traffic today was bad...">
So today anything that could possibly go wrong did.  It was just one of those days.  I don't want to relive it and pretty sure nobody wants to read because I bet at least 5 people who read this had an equally crap-ass day.  Especially the people who died on the highway.  Holy crap, I can't believe a huge accident pearlridge (which is to Honolulu like Guelph is to Waterloo or T-town to NorthD) caused horrible traffic in the actual city.  It took me an hour to get from the UH to Sidestreet Inn (which is like SPUC to Uptown Loo or my old house to downtown T-town)</lj-cut>

Ew.  A cockroach died in my razor... and I've packed up all my extras!  eww ew ew ewe w ew ew ew....  Okay... I'm going to start cleaning and bleaching so there's no more.

Did I mention I have no emails or phone mail messages except from my mother?  UGH!

(shite, this doesn't look right... no it really doesn't.  But writing "ha ha to one of you" sounds pathetic.  And it does have more satisfaction than not writing anything at all.  I wish I was where I was supposed to be this week.)

Damn it.  I failed.

Alright, I'll be sending out my usual big honking pile of postcards to people who are nice and keep me updated enough about them that I know their current address and that they're sick of school.

So I just called South Delta Secondary... They sent me on long-distance phone calling frenzy which led me back to them. Assholes. You're the one responsible for mailing me my diploma. I spent 5 fucking years at your damn school- give me a freaking piece of paper saying it. I suggest that if you graduated in 2003 and haven't received your Dogwood Diploma (which is approx. 100% minus the principal's daughter), call and be an ass. I can't stand South Delta, especially after I got badmouthed for going to UW, "kicked out" in April for appreciating poetry, and general discrepancies with administration there (like the time principal "didn't threaten me" when I wanted switch out of a class because I was being "political" - bah). Any reason to call and be bitch sounds good to me. A grad of 2004? Make sure to get mad if you don't get your diploma after Aug. 1st. You should have it in your hot grubby hands. Animosity? Yes.

I just got back from my trip from the North Shore.   I looove the North Shore.  Over anywhere else in Hawai'i, I'd live in the splendor of Haleiwa.  mmmmm  with the waves and green-ness and the lack of tourists and Chanel stores.

Well, I'm back in the concrete jungle of Honolulu.  I have to start fasting in three hours.  Blah.  I'm getting my wisdom teeth out early tomorrow morning.  Yeahhhhh.   

4 more days 4 more days!! :D  I just finished packing.  I have waaaay too much stuff.  I'm supposed to go home with at least half a suitcase empty.  Heh.  Doesn't look like it's going to happen!  Serves me right for buying at fiberfill matress thing... but I'm satisfied with the knowledge that I will have the comfies bed at spuc.  heheheheheheheh.

I'm trying to finish all my alcohol before I leave here.  Damn it.  I think this is the first time I've ever complained about having too many bottles.  Wait no.  There was that time my mom donated me a whole case of <del>shit beer</del> kokanee and wouldn't give me anything else until it was finished.  (shakes fist)

(cries) I sound like an alcoholic.  I've had 16 bottles since I got here.  And there's still 6 of them left.  Bwaaaaah.

Yeah!  Tommorrow is my last day of work!!!!!!!!  And I'm feeling better :D :D  After tomorrow is finished I can finally enjoy what Hawai'i is all about!!!  Shopping!

Yes I know.  I will go to the beach... only to go buy swimsuits.  It's quite sad.  Very sad.  Must spend co-op money.  I have no cards though... I lost my entire wallet and a bunch of letters I needed to send in a exhausted overheated mess.

Anyways... it's funny how everyone's home now.  I'm kinda glad in a way- everyone can return to being <del>sane</del> less insane.  I said goodbye to <lj user="habituating">  and seven of his drunk friends for at least five minutes.  Heh heh.  Glad to know Alcatraz is living up to it's traditions.

What else to say?  uhhh...?  Still not finished work report.  I'm glad I reread the guidelines and found out it only needs to be between 1500 - 2000 not 2500 - 3200.  I have no idea where I got those numbers from... Must have been in another overheated daze.

I'm going to die in the summer aren't I?

(though not advised) *** No ex-boyfriend. None. Zero. No Shanes. No Seans. No K/Chrises. Not even the mention of the ill-fated one. Zip!!!
